article.headline: Bassett carries Weber St. past Maine-Fort Kent 82-36
article.linkText: Bassett carries Weber St. past Maine-Fort Kent 82-36
article.story: OGDEN, Utah -- — Dontay Bassett came off the bench to score 13 points to lead Weber State to an 82-36 win over Maine-Fort Kent on Saturday. Zahir Porter had 11 points for Weber State (9-1), which earned its fourth straight home victory. Koby McEwen added 10 points. Jamison Overton had 10 points. Michat Petty had nine points of the USCAA member Bengals.
